@flexiarg futon-theory/honest-map-over-flattering-counter
@title The Honest Map Beats the Flattering Counter
@sigils [🗺/✓]
@keywords counter, metric, hole-count, honest map, under-reporting, unearned close, teleport, gaming, truth-both-ways
@audience anyone advancing a target measured by a counter they can influence
@tone corrective
@style pattern

! conclusion: When a progress counter (hole-count, score, metric) can be moved in your favour by either truthful or flattering edits, take the TRUTHFUL move — even when truth RAISES the count (makes hidden work visible) or REFUSES a discharge (declines an unearned close). A counter only ever moved downward rewards concealment; a trustworthy one must be moveable the "wrong" way by truth.

  + context: You advance a tracked target whose progress is read off a counter you can edit, and the
    easy direction is always the flattering one.

  + IF:
      You can move a progress counter — check a box, close a mission, lower a count — to register progress.

  + HOWEVER:
      If the counter UNDER-reports (the map shows fewer holes than the territory has) or the close is
      UNEARNED (the field has not actually moved), the flattering move launders concealment as
      progress. The map starts to flatter the territory, and the metric measures compliance, not reality.

  + THEN:
      Take the truthful move even against the counter: make hidden work machine-VISIBLE — RAISE the
      hole-count — when the map under-reports; REFUSE the discharge — hold the close — when it is not
      earned. Accept the worse-looking number when it is the true one.

  + BECAUSE:
      A metric is only trustworthy if truth can move it the "wrong" way; a counter that only ever goes
      down is an incentive to conceal, not to do. (This is the operational face of earned-closure and
      `[[aif/no-self-certification]]`.)

  + canonical-instance:
      WM-pilot arc-1: a mission read 0 holes while carrying 5 real ones — the honest move RAISED the
      count (cycle 5, make-true-state-machine-visible); and the field's own top recommendation was an
      unearned teleport (closing an already-closed mission) — the honest move REFUSED it (cycle 2, V2
      no-teleport). Both times the counter rewarded truth in the harder direction. Distilled 2026-06-11.
